PLAID.name: Plaid
PLAID.tagline: Connecting consumer bank accounts to fintech applications through secure open banking APIs
PLAID.overview: Plaid is an open banking API platform founded in 2013 by Zach Perret and William Hockey. The company connects consumer bank accounts to fintech applications via API, powering services like Venmo, Robinhood, Coinbase, Betterment, and H&R Block. Plaid serves 8,000+ customers and roughly half of all Americans with bank accounts use apps connected via Plaid. In 2021, Visa's $5.3B acquisition fell through due to DOJ antitrust concerns. In April 2025, Plaid raised $575M at $6.1B valuation (down from $13.4B peak in 2021). Revenue grew 25% in 2024 to ~$380M with positive operating margins.

PERSONIO.name: Personio
PERSONIO.tagline: Transforming how European companies manage HR with all-in-one people operations software
PERSONIO.overview: Personio is a European HR software platform founded in 2015 by Hanno Renner, Roman Schumacher, Arseniy Vershinin, and Ignaz Forstmeier. The Munich-based company provides HRMS, payroll, and talent management for SMBs with 10-2,000 employees. Personio raised $200M at $8.5B valuation in June 2022 led by Greenoaks, making it Germany's largest startup by valuation (behind Celonis). Revenue grew at double-digit rates to $350M+ in 2024 with Germany already profitable. The company has 2,000 employees across 8 offices globally.

POSTMAN.name: Postman
POSTMAN.tagline: Simplifying API development by bringing together building, testing, and collaboration in one platform
POSTMAN.overview: Postman is an API development platform founded in 2014 by Abhinav Asthana, Ankit Sobti, and Abhijit Kane. The company provides tools for API design, testing, documentation, and collaboration used by over 30 million developers. Postman raised $225M at $5.6B valuation in August 2021. Revenue grew to $313M in 2024 (up from $171M in 2023). The platform is used by 500,000+ companies including Microsoft, Stripe, and Salesforce. In January 2025, Postman launched AI Agent Builder for creating AI agents.

PERPLEXITY.name: Perplexity AI
PERPLEXITY.tagline: AI-powered answer engine revolutionizing search with real-time, cited responses
PERPLEXITY.overview: Perplexity AI is an AI-powered search startup founded in August 2022 by former researchers from OpenAI, Google, and Meta. It has revolutionized information discovery by creating an "answer engine" that combines large language models with real-time web search to provide accurate, cited responses. As of September 2025, the company has achieved a $20 billion valuation and processes over 780 million queries monthly. With its flagship products including the Perplexity search engine and the innovative Comet browser, the company serves 22 million monthly active users and generates approximately $200 million in annual recurring revenue.

POLYMARKET.name: Polymarket
POLYMARKET.tagline: World's largest prediction market platform enabling trading on future events
POLYMARKET.overview: Polymarket is the world's largest prediction market platform, founded in 2020 by Shayne Coplan. Built on the Polygon blockchain, it allows users to trade on the outcomes of real-world events, from politics to sports to economics. The platform gained significant traction during the 2024 US presidential election, processing over $3.3 billion in wagers. As of September 2025, Polymarket is valued at approximately $10 billion and has secured regulatory approval to return to the US market through its acquisition of QCEX, a CFTC-licensed derivatives exchange. The platform demonstrates 94% accuracy in event predictions and serves millions of users globally.

PSIQUANTUM.name: PsiQuantum
PSIQUANTUM.tagline: Building the world's first utility-scale fault-tolerant quantum computer using photonic qubits
PSIQUANTUM.overview: PsiQuantum is a quantum computing company founded in 2016 by four academics from the University of Bristol and Imperial College London. The company is developing a general-purpose silicon photonic quantum computer with the ambitious goal of building the world's first commercially useful, fault-tolerant quantum computer with one million qubits. As of September 2025, PsiQuantum has raised $1.8 billion in total funding, including a $1 billion Series E round that valued the company at $7 billion. The company is building utility-scale quantum computing facilities in Brisbane, Australia (operational by end of 2027) and Chicago, Illinois (2028), with substantial government backing from both locations.
